label: curveStyle
comment: The style or shape of the curve.

label: xMultiplier
comment: Multiplier for X-axis.

label: xUnit
comment: The X-axis units of measure.

label: y1Multiplier
comment: Multiplier for Y1-axis.

label: y1Unit
comment: The Y1-axis units of measure.

label: y2Multiplier
comment: Multiplier for Y2-axis.

label: y2Unit
comment: The Y2-axis units of measure.

label: y3Multiplier
comment: Multiplier for Y3-axis.

label: y3Unit
comment: The Y3-axis units of measure.

label: Curve
comment: The curve of  this curve data point.

label: xvalue
comment: The data value of the X-axis variable,  depending on the X-axis units.

label: y1value
comment: The data value of the  first Y-axis variable, depending on the Y-axis units.

label: y2value
comment: The data value of the second Y-axis variable (if present), depending on the Y-axis units.

label: y3value
comment: The data value of the third Y-axis variable (if present), depending on the Y-axis units.

label: description
comment: The description is a free human readable text describing or naming the object. It may be non unique and may not correlate to a naming hierarchy.

label: mRID
comment:
Master resource identifier issued by a model authority. The mRID is unique within an exchange context. Global uniqueness is easily achieved by using a UUID, as specified in RFC 4122, for the mRID. The use of UUID is strongly recommended.
For CIMXML data files in RDF syntax conforming to IEC 61970-552, the mRID is mapped to rdf:ID or rdf:about attributes that identify CIM object elements.

label: name
comment: The name is any free human readable and possibly non unique text naming the object.

label: SignalConfiguration
comment: The simulation configuration that is part of the simulation result.

label: SimulationEvents
comment: The simulation events that are part of the simulation result.

label: SimulationSettings
comment: The simulation settings that are part of the simulation result.

label: SimulationResult
comment: The simulation reslut to which this simulation result characteristic belongs to.

label: resultReference
comment: Reference to an artifact containing the data for the characteristic. This can be a reference to comma separated file or other serialization.

label: y1valueSignal
comment: The signal for y1value of the characteristic.

label: y2valueSignal
comment: The signal for y2value of the characteristic.

label: y3valueSignal
comment: The signal for y3value of the characteristic.
